Introduction

YOURS was a pre-debut project group under Deep Studio Entertainment. Their concept was that they were famous idols who returned to the past and lost their memories needing fans’ help to debut again.

The project was announced in early 2020 by the agency. They started recruiting trainees and each of them was announced from April to June 2020. The final number of trainees participating in the project was 17. They started their project on June 9, 2020.

The trainees were separated into different groups and were tasked to do dance covers and the fans would vote for who they wanted to see the most. The company started the official voting to decide the seven members that would be part of the debuting line-up on July 6, 2020. Fans voted for their top seven every day and the first seven trainees to hit 1,000,000 votes would debut. A trainee left at that time and was replaced by another one.

The group went on a hiatus in August 2020 due to Deep Studio Entertainment wanting to reorganize their plans. Despite this hiatus being short, some members left the project. Even after the group resumed their activities, members kept on leaving the project one by one.

YOURS released a pre-debut single titled ’My Memory is Yours’ on October 16, 2020. The music video is now sadly deleted from every streaming platform.

After more than half of the trainees left, the agency focused on releasing videos of their trainees showcasing their talents. Some new members were introduced but, instead of being called ’trainees’, were called ’rookies’, and added to the voting process.

In September of 2021, all of the original female trainees left the agency and the group. Shortly after, Deep Studio Entertainment deleted or rebranded all of their websites, announcing the end of the YOURS project.
